New circulars and information for local associations 16 December 2005 -- 5 January 2006 

  

LA/7702 2006 Women's annual meeting 

LA/7682, sent to LAs in early November gave details of all of the 2006 specialist group annual meetings and LAs were asked to publicise these meetings locally and organise local meetings to elect representatives, discuss motions and nominate members for election to national committees. Details of relevant deadlines were also included in LA/7682 and this circular sets out further information on the Women's annual meeting, including details of how to submit motions, nominate members for election and register representatives by the deadline of Monday 6 February 2006. All LAs are asked to actively seek representatives for this meeting. This is also being sent to the national Women's committee and local women's representatives.  (3 pages) 

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/html/la7702.html 

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/rtf/la7702.rtf 

  

LA/7701 2006 Fixed-term staff annual meeting 

LA/7682, sent to LAs in early November gave details of all of the 2006 specialist group annual meetings and LAs were asked to publicise these meetings locally and organise local meetings to elect representatives, discuss motions and nominate members for election to national committees. Details of relevant deadlines were also included in LA/7682 and this circular sets out further information on the fixed-term staff annual meeting, including details of how to submit motions, nominate members for election and register representatives by the deadline of Monday 6 March 2006.  All LAs are asked to actively seek representatives for this meeting. This is also being sent to the national FTS committee and local FTS representatives.  (3 pages) 

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/html/la7701.html 

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/rtf/la7701.rtf 

  

LA/7700 2006 Equal opportunities annual meeting 

LA/7682, sent to LAs in early November gave details of all of the 2006 specialist group annual meetings and LAs were asked to publicise these meetings locally and organise local meetings to elect representatives, discuss motions and nominate members for election to national committees.  Details of relevant deadlines were also included in LA/7682 and this circular sets out further information on the equal opportunities annual meeting, including details of how to submit motions, nominate members for election and register representatives by the deadline of Monday 20 February 2006. 

  

This year, a general equalities conference will be held on the day before the annual meeting, with equalities officers and other members with a general interest in equalities issues invited to attend. This will be a joint event, held with Natfhe equalities representatives and AUT members attending will also be invited to attend the morning plenary session of the annual meeting. Further information on this event will be sent out to LAs and local equalities representatives shortly. This information is also being sent to the national equal opportunities committee and local equalities representatives.  (3 pages) 

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/html/la7700.html 

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/rtf/la7700.rtf 

  

LA/7699 2006 Academic-related staff annual meeting 

LA/7682, sent to LAs in early November gave details of all of the 2006 specialist group annual meetings and LAs were asked to publicise these meetings locally and organise local meetings to elect representatives, discuss motions and nominate members for election to national committees.  Details of relevant deadlines were also included in LA/7682 and this circular sets out further information on the academic-related staff annual meeting, including details of how to submit motions, nominate members for election and register representatives by the deadline of Monday 6 February 2006.  All LAs are asked to actively seek representatives for this meeting.  This is also being sent to the national ARS committee and local ARS representatives. (3 pages) 

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/html/la7699.html 

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/rtf/la7699.rtf 

  

New Activist Development member training programme for winter/spring 2006 

The AUT's Activist Development member training programme for winter/spring 2006 has now been finalised. Courses, which cover a variety of topics including Advanced Negotiating, Personal Casework, Campaigning and Organising, and Leadership are open to all members and those wishing to attend should visit www.aut.org.uk/training for further information and to register. Alternatively, please contact Sheryl Hobbs, Training Officer at sheryl.hobbs@aut.org.uk. 

  

  

Links to new circulars are sent to LA secretaries.  If the address to which this email has been sent is not correct, or for any other changes in the details of local association officers and contacts please email mailto:hq@aut.org.uk 

  

